<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="58" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[140,1108,166,933]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,335,166,192]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis box="[185,330,166,192]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" reason="1">Description</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
Length of adults of both sexes (extended, alcohol material) ranging between 9.5 (♁) and 10.0- 
<quantity box="[440,544,202,229]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="13.5">13.5 mm</quantity>
(
<specimenCount box="[560,575,202,228]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
), width between 4.7 (♁) and 5.0- 
<quantity box="[963,1052,202,229]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="6.7">6.7 mm</quantity>
(
<specimenCount box="[1069,1084,202,228]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
); body broadest at thoracic shield. 
<typeStatus box="[514,621,237,263]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">Holotype</typeStatus>
ca 
<quantity box="[659,749,237,264]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[863,953,237,264]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="4.7">4.7 mm</quantity>
wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[140,1108,166,933]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">
Coloration (
<figureCitation box="[327,401,272,298]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="9.[140,212,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[140,1108,1083,1602]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[137,1110,1083,1602]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 3. Glomeris colorata sp. n., ♀ paratype from Tunisia, Siliana Gov.; habitus, dorsal view. (Photographed not to scale by I. Muratov)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3768974" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3768974/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[418,433,272,298]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="10.[140,212,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[263,982,975,1597]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 4. Glomeris colorata sp. n., ♁ holotype; A, habitus, dorsal view; B, pygidium, caudal view. A schematic, slightly too bright presentation of the colour pattern (del. J.-P. Mauriès)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3768976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3768976/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">4</figureCitation>
) variegated, mostly rather vivid, background usually dark brown, but sometimes mostly yellow due to expanded light spots. Head mostly light brown, evidently marbled near ocelli, with 1+1 and 2+2 small pallid spots against a light brown background just above antennal sockets; labrum pale yellowish; antennae largely dark brown, only tip pallid. Collum with a large, mostly marbled, yellowish central spot (
<figureCitation box="[291,363,448,474]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="9.[140,212,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[140,1108,1083,1602]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[137,1110,1083,1602]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 3. Glomeris colorata sp. n., ♀ paratype from Tunisia, Siliana Gov.; habitus, dorsal view. (Photographed not to scale by I. Muratov)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3768974" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3768974/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[379,396,448,474]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="10.[140,212,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[263,982,975,1597]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 4. Glomeris colorata sp. n., ♁ holotype; A, habitus, dorsal view; B, pygidium, caudal view. A schematic, slightly too bright presentation of the colour pattern (del. J.-P. Mauriès)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3768976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3768976/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">4</figureCitation>
). Thoracic shield with 2+2 large light spots, sometimes interconnected with a transversely oval marbled area in-between, but separated by a more or less evident, often incomplete, light axial line. Subsequent terga, except pygidium, with 1+1 more or less wide, light paramedian spots, usually arranged into clear stripes, a mostly interrupted and sometimes vague, light, axial line, and a pair of marbled, transversely oval, lateral areas. Pygidium with 1+1 light, paramedian, mostly coalesced spots (
<figureCitation box="[211,278,659,686]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="10.[140,212,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[263,982,975,1597]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 4. Glomeris colorata sp. n., ♁ holotype; A, habitus, dorsal view; B, pygidium, caudal view. A schematic, slightly too bright presentation of the colour pattern (del. J.-P. Mauriès)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3768976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3768976/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), less frequently nearly entirely light grey-brown. Venter and legs contrastingly light yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[140,1108,166,933]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">
Head usual, transverse; Tömösváry’s organ transversely oval, slightly shorter than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Golovatch &amp; Mauriès &amp; Akkari &amp; Stoev &amp; Geoffroy, 2009" authorityName="Golovatch &amp; Mauriès &amp; Akkari &amp; Stoev &amp; Geoffroy" authorityYear="2009" box="[169,370,765,792]" class="Diplopoda" family="Glomeridae" genus="Glomeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Glomerida" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="troglokabyliana" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[169,370,765,792]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">G. troglokabyliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[377,439,766,792]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; antennae long, antennomere 6 longest, 2.4-2.5 times long- er than wide; ocelli (4)5 black + 1 transparent, all convex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[140,1108,166,933]" box="[185,573,835,862]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">Collum with two transverse striae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[140,1108,166,933]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">
Thoracic shield with a narrow hyposchism almost reaching caudal tergal contour (
<figureCitation box="[148,239,906,933]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="11.[140,212,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[150,1098,755,1596]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[140,1108,744,1602]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 5. Glomeris colorata sp. n., ♁ holotype; A, thoracic shield and terga 3 and 4, lateral view; B, leg 17; C, leg 18; D, leg 19 (telopod), frontal view. – Scale bar: 0.5 mm (B-D); drawn not to scale (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3768978" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3768978/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
); four transverse striae, of which 1-2 anteriormost starting well in front of
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3768976" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3768976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3768976/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" startId="10.[140,212,1622,1644]" targetBox="[263,982,975,1597]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph blockId="10.[140,1107,1622,1676]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[140,241,1622,1644]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">Figure 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Golovatch &amp; Mauriès &amp; Akkari &amp; Stoev &amp; Geoffroy, 2009" authorityName="Golovatch &amp; Mauriès &amp; Akkari &amp; Stoev &amp; Geoffroy" authorityYear="2009" box="[249,405,1622,1643]" class="Diplopoda" family="Glomeridae" genus="Glomeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Glomerida" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colorata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[249,405,1622,1643]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">Glomeris colorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[413,467,1623,1644]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, ♁ holotype; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[601,620,1622,1644]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">A</emphasis>
, habitus, dorsal view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[836,853,1622,1644]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">B</emphasis>
, pygidium, caudal view. A schematic, slightly too bright presentation of the colour pattern (del. J.-P. Mauriès).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,166,651]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">
schism and crossing entire dorsum, the other two always abbreviated (
<figureCitation box="[925,1013,166,193]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="11.[140,212,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[150,1098,755,1596]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[140,1108,744,1602]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 5. Glomeris colorata sp. n., ♁ holotype; A, thoracic shield and terga 3 and 4, lateral view; B, leg 17; C, leg 18; D, leg 19 (telopod), frontal view. – Scale bar: 0.5 mm (B-D); drawn not to scale (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3768978" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3768978/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
); anteriormost stria only rarely slightly interrupted dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,166,651]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">
Tergum 3 relatively narrowly (
<figureCitation box="[537,626,237,264]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="11.[140,212,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[150,1098,755,1596]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[140,1108,744,1602]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 5. Glomeris colorata sp. n., ♁ holotype; A, thoracic shield and terga 3 and 4, lateral view; B, leg 17; C, leg 18; D, leg 19 (telopod), frontal view. – Scale bar: 0.5 mm (B-D); drawn not to scale (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3768978" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3768978/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
) and tergum 4 broadly rounded laterally. Tergal pilosity and mid-dorsal sinuosity absent. Pygidium usually with a completely regularly rounded caudal margin, only rarely extremely faintly sinuated medially at margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,166,651]" box="[185,992,378,406]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">
♁ leg 17 (
<figureCitation box="[299,383,378,405]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="11.[140,212,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[150,1098,755,1596]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[140,1108,744,1602]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 5. Glomeris colorata sp. n., ♁ holotype; A, thoracic shield and terga 3 and 4, lateral view; B, leg 17; C, leg 18; D, leg 19 (telopod), frontal view. – Scale bar: 0.5 mm (B-D); drawn not to scale (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3768978" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3768978/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
) with a low outer coxal lobe; telopodite 4-segmented.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,166,651]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">
♁ leg 18 (
<figureCitation box="[296,382,413,440]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="11.[140,212,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[150,1098,755,1596]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[140,1108,744,1602]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 5. Glomeris colorata sp. n., ♁ holotype; A, thoracic shield and terga 3 and 4, lateral view; B, leg 17; C, leg 18; D, leg 19 (telopod), frontal view. – Scale bar: 0.5 mm (B-D); drawn not to scale (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3768978" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3768978/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
) with a broadly subtriangular syncoxital notch; telopodite 4-segmented.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,166,651]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">
Telopods (
<figureCitation box="[303,396,483,510]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="11.[140,212,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[150,1098,755,1596]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[140,1108,744,1602]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 5. Glomeris colorata sp. n., ♁ holotype; A, thoracic shield and terga 3 and 4, lateral view; B, leg 17; C, leg 18; D, leg 19 (telopod), frontal view. – Scale bar: 0.5 mm (B-D); drawn not to scale (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3768978" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3768978/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Figs 5D</figureCitation>
) with a high, rather regularly rounded, bare, central syncoxital lobe flanked by two setose horns, latter each crowned with a minute bulb and a short setoid filament. Tarsus quite narrowly rounded apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,166,651]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,298,589,615]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis box="[185,293,589,615]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" reason="1">Remarks</emphasis>
:
</emphasis>
Based on the narrow tergum 3, 
<taxonomicName authority="Golovatch &amp; Mauriès &amp; Akkari &amp; Stoev &amp; Geoffroy, 2009" authorityName="Golovatch &amp; Mauriès &amp; Akkari &amp; Stoev &amp; Geoffroy" authorityYear="2009" box="[655,773,589,616]" class="Diplopoda" family="Glomeridae" genus="Glomeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Glomerida" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colorata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[655,773,589,616]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">G. colorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[780,840,590,616]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be attributed to the “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1909" box="[152,334,624,650]" class="Diplopoda" family="Glomeridae" genus="Stenopleuromeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Glomerida" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[152,334,624,650]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Stenopleuromeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<typeStatus box="[353,405,625,651]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">type</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
